# ============================================================================
# qnfo-skills — ALLOWLIST POLICY (ADR-026, hardened 2026-07-18 remediation)
# ============================================================================
# THIS REPOSITORY IS STRICTLY FOR SKILL FILES. NOTHING ELSE.
#
# Canonical skill layout (the ONLY structure permitted in this repo):
#   <skill-name>/SKILL.md              (required)
#   <skill-name>/scripts/*.js|*.py      (optional)
#   <skill-name>/references/*.md        (optional)
#   <skill-name>/templates/*            (optional)
#   <skill-name>/assets/*               (optional)
#
# Research projects, papers, WBS plans, PDFs, JSON data dumps, JIT ephemeral
# scripts, session closeout artifacts, and ANY project-specific content
# belong in a SEPARATE repository:
#   - QNFO/qnfo-research      (shared research repo for all projects), OR
#   - QNFO/<project-name>     (dedicated repo per large project)
# NEVER commit them here. See ADR-026 and ADR-027 for full policy.
#
# ============================================================================
# STEP 1: Default-deny everything at repository ROOT (anchored, non-recursive)
# ============================================================================
/*

# ============================================================================
# STEP 2: Explicitly allow root-level policy files
# ============================================================================
!/.gitignore
!/README.md
!/ADR-026-skills-only.md
!/ADR-027-research-separation.md
!/ADR-028-r2-immediate-write.md

# ============================================================================
# STEP 3: Explicitly allow the 9 known skill directories (root-anchored)
# ============================================================================
!/cloudflare/
!/code/
!/documents/
!/frontend-design/
!/git-github/
!/knowledge/
!/qnfo-agent/
!/research/
!/system/

# ============================================================================
# STEP 4: Defense-in-depth — inside allowed skill dirs, still block anything
# that looks like research/project/JIT ephemera (unanchored patterns apply
# at any depth within the allowed directories from Step 3).
# ============================================================================
**/*.pdf
**/*.pptx
**/*.docx
**/*.xlsx
**/*.csv
**/releases/
**/artifacts/
**/projects/
**/papers/
**/WBS*.md
**/wbs*.md
**/*-cryptanalysis.md
**/*-distribution-wbs.md
**/_*
**/__pycache__/
**/.wrangler/
**/*.log
**/*.err
**/*.sql
**/*.bat
**/*.dll
**/*.exe
**/*.pak
**/*.dat
**/*.bin
